03/03/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano met with Kosovo President Ibrahim Rugova on the second day of his visit to Kosovo on Tuesday (2 March).
The two officials discussed ways to boost bilateral ties and exchanged views on the process of integration into the EU and NATO, as well as on co-operation between Kosovo authorities and UNMIK.
Euro-Atlantic integration was on the agenda of Albanian Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami's meeting with his German counterpart, Joshka Fischer on Tuesday.
Islami, who is visiting Germany, also met with German Interior Minister Otto Schilly.
The two discussed the fight against organised crime, and Schilly pledged the German government's financial support for establishing an anti-trafficking centre in Vlore.(ATA, Albanian TV - 02/03/04)
